                    Method overloading

 With the help of method overloading , we can have multiple methods with the same name but different parameters

 Advantages of using it:
 1. Cleaner, more readable code
 2. flexibility for the end user

 How to do it:
 1. Change the data type of parameters
 2. Change the number of parameters
 3. Change the order of parameters

 Class Calculator{

 int method(int num1, int num2){
 return num1+num2;
 }
 int method(int num2, int num1){ //3.
 return num2+num1;
 }
 int method(double num1, double, num2){ // 1.
 return
 }
 int method(int num1, int num2, int num3){ // 2.
  return num1+num2;
  }
 }


 Rules:

 1. Methods should have same name but different parameters
 2. We cannot overload a method just by changing the return type
 3. We can overload a constructor by following the same rules












